# Overview
Unitext-manager provides a high level layer to work with [Unitex Corpus Processor](http://www-igm.univ-mlv.fr/~unitex/).
You should install [Pyunitex](https://github.com/moliware/pyunitex)

![Overview](http://labs.paradigmatecnologico.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/unitex_manager_overview.png)

# Easy to use

You will be able to apply this grammar by means of Unitex-manager with a few lines

![Simple grammar](http://labs.paradigmatecnologico.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/sample_grammar.png)

````
# Instanciate an object
unitexManager = UniteManager()

# Get tokens
tokens_result = unitexManager.tokenizer("Spain and england are different countries", "es")
print 'Tokens: ',tokens_result

# Apply POSTtagging
pos_tagging = unitexManager.postagger(tokens_result, "es")
print 'Pos tagging: ',pos_tagging

# Apply Grammar
grammar = unitexManager.grammar(tokens_result, pos_tagging, "es")
print '=> ',grammar
```

# Output

The output will be 
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><result><country>Spain</country><country>england</country></result> 
```

See Unitex-manager running:
````
